# Example environment variables for Google Sheets integration
# Put these values in .env.local (do NOT commit secrets to git)

# The ID of your Google Spreadsheet (already set as default in code)
GOOGLE_SPREADSHEET_ID=1FdT0BsJ37IVQkdaWagCC9Qs2Z3I-ADw4u-7gmbvnk08

# Service account JSON. You can provide it in two ways (both supported by route.ts):
#
# Option A (raw JSON): paste the JSON as a single-line string and escape any literal newlines
# Example:
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON='{"type":"service_account","project_id":"...","private_key":"-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\\n...\\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\\n","client_email":"your-sa@...gserviceaccount.com",...}'
#
# Option B (base64): base64-encode the JSON file content and paste the base64 string
# Example (Linux/Mac):
#   base64 sa-key.json | pbcopy
#   # then in .env.local:
#   GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=BASE64_STRING_HERE

# The route will auto-detect base64 and decode it, and will normalize escaped '\\n' into real newlines.

# Optional: If you deploy a Google Apps Script web app, set its URL here so the client posts directly to it
# Example:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUBMIT_URL="https://script.google.com/macros/s/XXXXXXXX/exec"
